<h1>FormElementComponent</h1>

<h2><code>&#123;&#123;uic-form-element&#125;&#125;</code></h2>

<div>

  <h2>Description</h2>

  <p>
    The <code>uic-form-element</code> component renders a <code>div</code> element
    containing a form element (<code>input</code> by default) and optionally
    adds a <code>label</code> element.
  </p>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-basic.hbs"}}

  <div>
    {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET form-element-component-basic}}
    {{uic-form-element value=value}}
    {{! END-SNIPPET }}
  </div>

</div>
<hr />
<div>

  <h2>Label</h2>

  <p>
    You can provide a label to the form element by adding a <code>label</code> attribute.
  </p>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-label.hbs"}}

  <div>
    {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET form-element-component-label}}
    {{uic-form-element
      label="Property name"}}
    {{! END-SNIPPET }}
  </div>

</div>

<hr />
<div>

  <h2>Type</h2>

  <p>
    You can provide a <code>type</code> attribute and it will be passed to the <code>input</code> element.
  </p>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-input-type.hbs"}}

  <div>
    {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET form-element-component-input-type}}
    {{uic-form-element
      label="Property name"
      type="number"}}
    {{! END-SNIPPET }}
  </div>

</div>

<hr />
<div>

  <h2>Placeholder</h2>

  <p>
    Placeholder attribute is supported.  You can provide a <code>placeholder</code>
    attribute and it will be passed to the <code>input</code> element.
  </p>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-placeholder.hbs"}}

  <div>
    {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET form-element-component-placeholder}}
    {{uic-form-element
      label="Property name"
      placeholder="Enter some text..."}}
    {{! END-SNIPPET }}
  </div>

</div>

<hr />

<div>

  <h2>Disabled</h2>

  <p>
    If you set the <code>disabled</code> attribute to true the <code>input</code>
    element will be disabled and the <code>disabled</code> class will be applied
    to the form-element component.
  </p>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-disabled.hbs"}}

  <div>
    {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET form-element-component-disabled}}
    {{uic-form-element
      disabled=true
      label="Property name"
      placeholder="This element is disabled!"}}
    {{! END-SNIPPET }}
  </div>
</div>

<hr />

<div>

  <h2>Read-only</h2>

  <p>
    If you set the <code>readOnly</code> attribute to true the <code>input</code>
    element will be disabled and the <code>read-only</code> class will be applied
    to the form-element component.
  </p>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-readonly.hbs"}}

  <div>
    {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET form-element-component-readonly}}
    {{uic-form-element
      readonly=true
      label="Property name"
      placeholder="This element is readonly..."}}
    {{! END-SNIPPET }}
  </div>

</div>

<hr />

<div>

  <h2>Form Element ID</h2>

  <p>
    If you provide a value to the <code>formElementId</code> attribute this will
    be used for the <code>id</code> attribute of the <code>input</code> element.
  </p>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-id.hbs"}}

  <div>
    {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET form-element-component-id}}
    {{uic-form-element
      form-element-id="my-unique-element-id"
      label="Property name"
      placeholder="Enter some text..."}}
    {{! END-SNIPPET }}
  </div>

</div>

<div class="panel">

  <h2>Template block</h2>
  <p>
    By default, the <code>uic-form-element</code> component will render an
    <code>input</code> element.  If you want to render a custom element, you
    can pass a template block to the component.
  </p>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-checkbox.hbs"}}

  <div>
    {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET form-element-component-checkbox}}
    {{#uic-form-element label="Property Name"}}
      {{uic-check-box}}
    {{/uic-form-element}}
    {{! END-SNIPPET }}
  </div>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-select.hbs"}}

  <div>
    {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET form-element-component-select}}

    {{#uic-form-element label="Property Name"}}
      <select>
        <option>One</option>
        <option>Two</option>
        <option>Three</option>
      </select>
    {{/uic-form-element}}
    {{! END-SNIPPET }}
  </div>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-textarea.hbs"}}

  <div>
    {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET form-element-component-textarea}}
    {{#uic-form-element label="Property Name" readOnly=readOnly}}
      <textarea></textarea>
    {{/uic-form-element}}
    {{! END-SNIPPET }}
  </div>

  <h2>Block params</h2>

  <p>
    The block template has an object available to it that provides the following parameters.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <code>id</code>: This is the value of the <code>formElementId</code> attribute if provided, or an auto-generated id value.
    </li>
  </ul>

  {{code-panel name="form-element-component-params.hbs"}}

</div>
